  "problem_spec": {
    "summary": "A base-$b$ number is built from a length-$L$ ramp of digits $(t,t+1,\\dots,t+L-1)$. Divisibility by a prime power $p^k$ is exposed by the digit-sum reduction $b\\equiv 1\\pmod{p^k}$, while divisibility by a distinct prime $q$ is exposed by an order-3 cycle reduction coming from $q\\mid (b^2+b+1)$ (so $b^3\\equiv 1\\pmod q$). Exactness ($p^{k+1}\\nmid N_t$ and $q^2\\nmid N_t$) is forced by one-step lifts to $p^{k+1}$ and $q^2$, the latter using a 3-cycle lift via $b^3=1+q w$.",
